===Etymology===
Middle English ''heven'' < Old English ''[[heofon]]'', possibly < Proto-Germanic *''[[khiminaz]]'' < Proto-Indo-European base ''*kem-''/''*kam-'' (“to cover”).

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|hĕv'ən}}
*{{IPA|/ˈhɛvən/}}
*{{SAMPA|/"hEv@n/}}

===Noun===
'''heaven''' (''plural:'' [[heavens]])

# The [[sky]].
# (''theology'') The [[paradise]] of the [[afterlife]] in certain [[:w:religion|religions]].
# The home of the [[god]] or the [[deity]].
#: ''Mommy’s gone to '''heaven''' to be with God.''

